## Boas Práticas de Logging

### Correto vs Incorreto

```csharp
// ✅ CORRETO — message template estruturado
_logger.LogInformation(
    "Order {OrderId} created for customer {CustomerId} with total {Total:C}",
    order.Id, order.CustomerId, order.Total);

// ❌ ERRADO — string interpolation (perde a estrutura)
_logger.LogInformation($"Order {order.Id} created for customer {order.CustomerId}");

// ✅ CORRETO — mascarar dados sensíveis
_logger.LogInformation("User {Email} logged in",
    email[..3] + "***@" + email.Split('@')[1]);

// ❌ ERRADO — logar dados sensíveis
_logger.LogInformation("Password {Password} verified for {Email}", password, email);

// ✅ CORRETO — nível apropriado
_logger.LogDebug("Cache hit for key {Key}", key);
_logger.LogInformation("Order {OrderId} completed", orderId);
_logger.LogWarning("Retry attempt {Attempt} for service {Service}", attempt, service);
_logger.LogError(ex, "Failed to process order {OrderId}", orderId);
_logger.LogCritical("Database connection lost, shutting down");
```

